Question: What's your opinion on parents who let their 10 year old play games like Grand Theft Auto, Call of Duty, Battlefield, Saints Row, Manhunt, Gears of War, Metal Gear Solid, The Suffering, Far Cry, The Last of US and Fallout?
Answer:
Personally my dad never bought those kind of console gaming systems because he believe that it's a waste of time and ruins the development of a children's brain. He also read into studies that shows the negative effect of those kind of games to children.
  
  Then when I took AP psych we did a whole lesson on the psychological experiments they've done on games like that with kids. & it was awful seeing how in 10 minutes they were doing what they saw on a screen. People don't realize children are like sponges.
  
  There was also an interview with Kevin spacey who was actually one of the main people who were involved in the creation of these games, and he even mentions how most of these games that are created are meant to train young minds with military tactics and strategy to prepare us for the future.
  
  So would I let my kid play this at 10,no definitely not. They will have a higher tendency to be disrespectful, rude, & lazy towards their parents.
  
  They also did a study that proved most gamers have become a gamer due to bully or teasing - they use it as an outlet. I don't want my kid to learn how to cope with issues by just turning on the Xbox and shooting people, that's how school shootings happens guys.
